 I said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, what is the greatest sin?\u201d The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cTo set up a partner alongside Allah, even though He alone created you.\u201d I said, \u201cWhat is next?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cTo kill your child, fearing\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":3135,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/05\/06\/adultery-accusations-need-proof\/","url_meta":{"origin":31731,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Zina: Accusers must bring proof, or be punished","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 6, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: Hilal ibn Umayyah was with the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, and he accused his wife of adultery with Sharik ibn Sahma. The Prophet said, \u201cBring proof, otherwise the punishment is on your back.\u201d Hilal said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, if any one of us\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":11996,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/02\/03\/punishment-zina-riba\/","url_meta":{"origin":31731,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Warning: Adultery and usury widespread, punishment follows","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 3, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Mas\u2019ud reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cAdultery and usury do not become prevalen